Class ArchiveUnit

  • Object
    • DataObjectPackageElement
      • DataObjectPackageIdElement
        • ArchiveUnit

  • public class ArchiveUnit
extends DataObjectPackageIdElement
    The Class ArchiveUnit.

    Class for SEDA element ArchiveUnit. It contains management and content metadata and links to DataObjects.

      • toSedaXml

        public void toSedaXml(SEDAXMLStreamWriter xmlWriter,
                      boolean imbricateFlag,
                      SEDALibProgressLogger sedaLibProgressLogger)
               throws SEDALibException,
                      InterruptedException
        Export the ArchiveUnit in XML expected form for the SEDA Manifest.
        Parameters:
        xmlWriter - the SEDAXMLStreamWriter generating the SEDA manifest
        imbricateFlag - indicates if the manifest ArchiveUnits are to be exported in imbricate mode (true) or in flat mode (false)
        sedaLibProgressLogger - the progress logger or null if no progress log expected
        Throws:
        SEDALibException - if the XML can't be written
        InterruptedException - if export process is interrupted

      • toSedaXmlFragments

        public String toSedaXmlFragments()
        Export the elements of ArchiveUnit that can be edited without changing the structure. This is in XML expected form for the SEDA Manifest but in String.
        Returns:
        the XML elements in String format

      • idFromSedaXml

        public static String idFromSedaXml(SEDAXMLEventReader xmlReader,
                                   DataObjectPackage dataObjectPackage,
                                   SEDALibProgressLogger sedaLibProgressLogger)
                            throws SEDALibException,
                                   InterruptedException
        Import the ArchiveUnit in XML expected form from the SEDA Manifest in the ArchiveTransfer and return it's id in ArchiveTransfer.
        Parameters:
        xmlReader - the SEDAXMLEventReader reading the SEDA manifest
        dataObjectPackage - the DataObjectPackage to be completed
        sedaLibProgressLogger - the progress logger
        Returns:
        the inDataPackageObjectId of the read ArchiveUnit, or null if not an ArchiveUnit
        Throws:
        SEDALibException - if the XML can't be read
        InterruptedException - if export process is interrupted

      • fromSedaXmlFragments

        public void fromSedaXmlFragments(String fragments)
                          throws SEDALibException
        Import the elements of ArchiveUnit that can be edited without changing the structure. This is in XML expected form for the SEDA Manifest but in String.
        Parameters:
        fragments - the XML elements in String format
        Throws:
        SEDALibException - if the XML can't be read or don't have expected mandatory field - Content
